	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> <date>September 16<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1862</date>.</p>
				<p>Reverend Sir&#44;</p>
				<p>In consequence of the advertisement<lb/> of the Hebrew Ed. Society of your<lb/> city I have this day directed a letter<lb/> to <persName>Mr. I. Binswanger</persName>&#44; in which<lb/> I reported him on the course of studies<lb/> I pursued&#44; the testimonials I hold<lb/> and how long&#44; where and in what<lb/> occupation I spent the time of my<lb/> sojourn in this country.</p>
				<p>After taking the liberty of referring<lb/> also to you&#44; Rev. Sir&#44; I applied for<lb/> the vacant situation&#44; mentioned in<lb/> the above advertisement&#44; provided<lb/> stipulations and salary be acceptable.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Now&#44; Rev. Sir&#44; I know the great<lb/> authority you exercise and the great<lb/> influence you have with the Board<lb/> of the above school.  I likewise<lb/> flatter myself to be known to</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>you as fully worthy of filling the<lb/> above situation to the entire satis&#45;<lb/>faction of the Board and community.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Would you therefore interfere in<lb/> my behalf and recommend me for<lb/> the above situation&#63;</p>
				<p>I know your noble character and<lb/> the interest you take in the promotion<lb/> of our sacred religion too well&#44; as<lb/> to entertain for one moment the<lb/> fear&#44; that the little literary con&#45;<lb/>troversy we had last year which<lb/> was of a strictly private nature and<lb/> did not spread into publicity<lb/> would induce you&#44; not to exert your<lb/> influence in my and our sacred<lb/> religion&#39;s favor&#44; for you assuredly<lb/> know that capable men are quite<lb/> scarce in this country.</p>
				<p>I have not the least doubt that<lb/> I cannot only in my sphere as a</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>teacher of the above school&#44; but also<lb/> as a contribution to orthodox journals<lb/> on religious questions and matters be<lb/> of salutary influence.</p>
				<p>Hoping you will comply with my<lb/> request and wishing you <add>Hebrew</add> with<lb/> all my heart&#44; I am&#44; Rev. Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">yours most obediently</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">L. Buttenwieser</persName></p>
				<p>My direction is&#58;</p>
				<p><persName role="author">L. Buttenwieser</persName>&#44;</p>
				<p>care of <persName>Messrs Heller Bros &#38; Co.</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Cincinnati O.</placeName></p>
		</body>
